description:
Do you remember the most recent sermon you heard?

Maybe you do, but most of us quickly forget the sermon right after hearing it. However, try remembering the last story you heard. Stories are easily remembered because they paint pictures in our minds, don’t they?

Visual storytelling is one of the most effective ways to engage everyone in the message we want them to hear. It is not only about the drawings and pictures but also about how you deliver the story using your voice and gestures to help the listeners paint pictures in their imaginations.

View the video to learn more about the power of storytelling.
